Defining the outcome variable

The main objective is to predict whether a hypernatremic patient recovers or not. Recovery is defined as sodium levels will falling by 6 to 10 units and/or falling below 145 within the first 24 hours. In other words, recovery includes the case where the sodium falls from 160 to 154 and the case where it falls from 147 to 144. (Why did we define it as such?)

A total of 1902 patients met the inclusion criteria. Among this group, 955 patients that fit our above definition of recovery (i.e.label = 1) and 947 that didnt (i.e.label = 0).
